":"1598–Deceased","1569–Male":"1569–Deceased","1569":"1569","1566":"1566","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1641":"1641","1672":"1672","1649":"1649","1603":"1603","Ireland":"Ireland","Donegal or Antrim, Ireland":"County Antrim, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mchugh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Conal, Sinead, Brigid, Conall, Cormac, Eamon, Eamonn, Fintan, Kieran, Malachy, Patrick Sean.","Irish and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Aodha</b> or <b>Mac Aoidh</b> ‘son of <i>Aodh</i>’, an old personal name meaning ‘fire’, originally the name of a pagan god. Thus the name has the same origin as   McKay  ,   McGee  , and   McCoy  . See also   Hughes   3."],"variants":[{"name":"McKay","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Aoidh</b> ‘son of <i>Aodh</i>’, an old personal name meaning ‘fire’. Etymologically, this is the same name as   McKee  ,   McGee  ,   McCoy  , and   McHugh  .","History: This is the surname of several Irish and Scottish families, including Clan Mackay, a Highland clan traditionally associated with Sutherland in the far northwest of Scotland."]},{"name":"McCue","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Clancy, Niall.","Irish (northern): variant of   McHugh   (see   McCoy  )."]},{"name":"Molloy","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Brigid, Eamon, Fintan, Brid, Caitlin, Colm, Cormac, Dermot, Ethna, Kevin Patrick, Kieran.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maolmhuaidh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Maolmhuadh</i>’, a personal name based on <i>maol</i> ‘youth, chieftain’ and <i>muad</i> ‘noble, glorious’."]}]},{"name":"Turlough","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Toirdhealbhach ."],"variants":[{"name":"Toirdhealbhach","meanings":["Traditional name, apparently from a byname meaning ‘instigator’, from <i>toirdhealbh</i> ‘prompting’. It was the name of a High King of Ireland who died in  1156 ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1355925,"age":34,"year":"1603","julianDay":2306544,"description":"Accession of James I. Surrender of Hugh O'Neill. Enforcement of English Law in Ireland.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1355926,"age":72,"year":"1641","julianDay":2320424,"description":"Great Catholic-Gaelic rebellion for return of lands, later joined by Old English Catholics in Ireland. Under leadership of Irish chieftain, Rory O'More, conspiracy was formed to seize Dublin and expel the English. English settlers were driven out of Ulster. Catholics hold 59% of land in Ireland.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1355927,"age":80,"year":"1649","julianDay":2323346,"description":"The Protestant Lord Protector of England, Oliver Cromwell, landed at Dublin. His troops killed 2,000 men. A great part of lands in Munster, Leinster and Ulster (Drogheda and Wexford) was confiscated and divided among the English soldiers.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1355928,"age":103,"year":"1672","julianDay":2331746,"description":"Over 6,000 Irish boys and women sold as slaves since England gained control of Jamaica.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Turlough Mchugh was born in 1569, in County Antrim, Ireland. He had at least 2 sons with Agnes Campbell."},"et":{"1569–":"1569–Surnud","1566–Female":"1566–Surnud","1597–Male":"1597–Surnud","1598–Male":"1598–Surnud","1569–Male":"1569–Surnud","1569":"1569","1566":"1566","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1641":"1641","1672":"1672","1649":"1649","1603":"1603","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Donegal or Antrim, Ireland":"County Antrim, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1569–":"1569–Kuollut","1566–Female":"1566–Kuollut","1597–Male":"1597–Kuollut","1598–Male":"1598–Kuollut","1569–Male":"1569–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1566":"1566","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1641":"1641","1672":"1672","1649":"1649","1603":"1603","Ireland":"Irlanti","Donegal or Antrim, Ireland"